<li id="cite_note-Paul_Arthur_Schilpp.2C_editor_1951_730.E2.80.93746-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Paul_Arthur_Schilpp.2C_editor_1951_730.E2.80.93746_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paul_Arthur_Schilpp.2C_editor_1951_730.E2.80.93746_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation" id="CITEREFPaul_Arthur_Schilpp.2C_editor1951">Paul Arthur Schilpp, editor (1951), <i>Albert Einstein: Philosopher-Scientist, Volume II</i>, New York: Harper and Brothers Publishers (Harper Torchbook edition), pp.&#160;730–746</span>His non-scientific works include: <i>About Zionism: Speeches and Lectures by Professor Albert Einstein</i> (1930), "Why War?" (1933, co-authored by <a href="Sigmund_Freud" title="Sigmund Freud">Sigmund Freud</a>), <i>The World As I See It</i> (1934), <i>Out of My Later Years</i> (1950), and a book on science for the general reader, <i><a href="The_Evolution_of_Physics" title="The Evolution of Physics">The Evolution of Physics</a></i> (1938, co-authored by <a href="Leopold_Infeld" title="Leopold Infeld">Leopold Infeld</a>).</span></li>
